openmediavault-oar (8.1.0~beta4-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Package the Python modules with dh-python: bytecode is compiled on the
    target at install time and no stale __pycache__ is shipped.
  * Report each pool's mount point in the status and block deletion from
    the UI while the filesystem is mounted, not only while it is referenced
    by an fstab entry.
  * Housekeeping: tidy the notifyPool config-object assignment, correct the
    activity-summary docstring, bump Standards-Version to 4.6.2 and align
    the documented openmediavault dependency with debian/control.

 -- carbrf <carbrf@gmail.com>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 15:00:00 -0400

openmediavault-oar (8.1.0~beta3-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Never leave a RAID5 tier without write-hole protection. During grow
    finalization the write-intent bitmap is dropped before PPL is
    restored; if re-enabling PPL fails, an internal bitmap is now re-added
    as a fallback instead of leaving the array unprotected.
  * Serialize pool finalization. The boot-time finalize unit, the per-pool
    finalize unit and the manual RPC can all target one pool; a per-pool
    lock now ensures only one runs the pvresize/lvextend/fs-grow/reap
    sequence at a time.
  * Ship the systemd units from /usr/lib/systemd/system and enable them,
    with a systemd daemon-reload, from the package maintainer scripts, so
    the on-demand finalize unit is always visible without a reboot.

 -- carbrf <carbrf@gmail.com>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 14:00:00 -0400

openmediavault-oar (8.1.0~beta2-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Drop F2FS support. f2fs cannot be grown online, so the finalize step
    failed on the (mounted) pool a grow leaves behind and wedged the pool
    in the pending-finalize state. Supported file systems are now BTRFS,
    EXT4, XFS and JFS.
  * Replace/repair now reaps the retired disk. After a hot-replace or a
    repair, background finalization removes the old disk's stale array
    members, zeroes their superblocks and clears the OAR partition labels,
    so pool discovery no longer double-counts the replaced disk.

 -- carbrf <carbrf@gmail.com>  Mon, 06 Jul 2026 13:00:00 -0400

